<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-31T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="598" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/390</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-31T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It has been reported great damage has been done Cuban Railroad Company
                            line between Santiago and San Luis and San Luis and Marti. The
                            Department is disturbed, as we understand that the censorship is so
                            strict that no information is getting through.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>